        page_content="A:  Concentration  risk  arises  from  over-exposure  to  single  borrower,  sector,  geography,  or  \nproduct.\n \nBanks\n \nmust\n \nset\n \ninternal\n \nconcentration\n \nlimits\n \nand\n \nmonitor\n \nunder\n \nICAAP.\n Source:  Basel  Pillar  2  Concentration  Risk  Guidelines;  RBI  ICAAP  Guidelines   Q87:  What  is  ICAAP  and  which  banks  must  prepare  it?  A:  Internal  Capital  Adequacy  Assessment  Process  (ICAAP)  requires  banks  to  assess  all  \nmaterial\n \nrisks\n \nbeyond\n \nPillar\n \n1\n \nand\n \nmaintain\n \nadequate\n \ncapital.\n \nAll\n \nscheduled\n \ncommercial\n \nbanks\n \nmust\n \nsubmit\n \nannually.\n Source:  RBI  Basel  III  Pillar  2  Guidelines   Q88:  What  is  Stress  Testing  and  what  scenarios  must  Indian  banks  test?  A:  Banks  must  conduct  stress  tests  for  credit  risk  (NPA  spike),  market  risk  (interest  rate  shocks),  \nand\n \nliquidity\n \nrisk\n \n(outflow\n \nscenarios).\n \nSubmitted\n \nas\n \npart\n \nof\n \nICAAP\n \nto\n \nRBI.\n Source:  RBI  Stress  Testing  Guidelines   Q89:  What  is  Model  Risk  and  how  should  it  be  governed?  A:  Model  risk  arises  from  incorrect  or  misused  quantitative  models  (credit  scoring,  ALM,  pricing).  \nBanks\n \nshould\n \nhave\n \nmodel\n \nvalidation,\n \ndocumentation,\n \nand\n \nindependent\n \nreview\n \nprocesses.\n Source:  Basel  Model  Risk  Principles;  RBI  Risk  Management  Guidelines   Q90:  What  is  the  compliance  function's  role  under  RBI  and  Basel  guidelines?  A:  The  compliance  function  independently  ensures  adherence  to  laws,  regulations,  and  internal  \npolicies.\n \nIt\n \nreports\n \ndirectly\n \nto\n \nthe\n \nBoard/MD\n \nand\n \nis\n \nseparate\n \nfrom\n \ninternal\n \naudit.\n \nNon-compliance\n \nfindings\n \nmust\n \nbe\n \nescalated\n \npromptly.\n Source:  Basel  Compliance  Principles;  RBI  Corporate  Governance  Guidelines,  2021",
